<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-76-0098 </DOCNO><TEXT>The invention deals with a lighter designed as a catamaran or trimaranto be used as a skimmer for oil spills. The space between the parallelhull structures serves as a feeding channel for oil spills into the skimmersystem. The system consist of an opening for oil spills into the variouschannels equipped with traps for the separation of oil/water substances.In addition, the system consists of storage tanks for reclaimed oil andan outlet for water. 2 drawings.</TEXT></DOC>